              "type": "text",
              "text": {
                "content": "Authors hypothesize that there is a relationship between student affect, engagement and their learning outcomes. Authors look into ASSISTments data and found boredom during exercises to be negatively correlated with performance. However, boredom during a tutoring session was positively correlated with performance. ",
